  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\nCurrently verification of historic block signatures is done in `RocksDbDatabase` which means it blocks the single storage thread while performing the verification and has to load a state from the database to be able to verify against.\n\nWe should do the verification in the beacon chain service as part of `HistoricalBlockFetcher` before sending to the storage service.  It already has a finalized state in memory and won't block other operations that need to update the database.",
